news.title: Union cabinet clears three new metro stretches in Delhi, including Central Vista corridor
news.para: Delhi's infrastructure receives a significant upgrade with the Union Cabinet's approval for three new Metro corridors. A key stretch will connect RK Ashram Marg to Indraprastha, enhancing access to Kartavya Bhavans and India Gate. Two other corridors will improve airport and south Delhi connectivity.

news.title: NBCC starts its real estate operations in Dubai
news.para: NBCC India has begun overseas real estate operations in Dubai. A subsidiary has acquired land for a mixed-use development. The company also signed an MoU with Mumbai Port Authority. This partnership will focus on developing a CGO Complex on port land.

news.title: Beijing further eases home buying curbs
news.para: Beijing has taken a significant step to energize its real estate sector by easing home purchasing rules. Non-residents will now need just one year of income tax payments to qualify, instead of two. In an encouraging development for larger families, there’s an allowance to acquire an extra residence in the heart of the city.

news.title: J Estates enters into senior living housing segment
news.para: J Estates is venturing into the senior living market, launching three major initiatives in Gurugram. Comprising approximately 450 units, these projects will embody luxury and comfort, with a total investment of ₹2,100 crore.

news.title: Japan's Sapporo Holdings to sell real estate business to KKR-PAG group for $3.1 billion
news.para: Sapporo Holdings is selling its real estate business to a consortium led by KKR and PAG. The deal is valued at 477 billion yen. This move follows pressure from activist investors. Sapporo will use the funds for growth and debt reduction. The real estate market in Japan is attracting investor interest.

news.title: Embassy REIT sells 3.76 lakh sq ft space in Manyata Park in Bengaluru for ₹530 crore
news.para: Embassy REIT has offloaded prime office space in Bengaluru for an impressive ₹530 crore. The acquisition by EAAA Alternatives' Rental Yield Plus fund strengthens their presence in the renowned Embassy Manyata Business Park.

news.title: Navi Mumbai International Airport set to commence operations on December 25
news.para: The Navi Mumbai International Airport is set to begin commercial flights on Thursday. This new airport will significantly cut travel times and boost tourism. It will also attract major investments to the region.

news.title: Issue clear norms, Karnataka-RERA chief tells government as OC–CC confusion continues
news.para: K-Rera chairman Rakesh Singh has urged the Karnataka government to issue clear guidelines on occupancy and completion certificates due to conflicting interpretations across various laws. This regulatory ambiguity is causing confusion and harming homebuyers in Bengaluru, with local bodies interpreting provisions differently, leading to delays and potential exploitation by developers.

news.title: Claim GST refund from government on cancelled flat deal: West Bengal REAT
news.para: A home buyer cannot claim GST refund from a developer after a terminated purchase deal; the claim must be made with the GST authority. The West Bengal Real Estate Appellate Tribunal ruled this, allowing a developer to deduct GST paid on behalf of an allottee. The tribunal set aside a penalty imposed by the regulatory authority.

news.title: RLDA gets ₹2,250 crore bid for 2.5-acre land parcel in Mumbai
news.para: The Railway Land Development Authority has secured its highest bid ever. A prime 2.5-acre plot in Mahalaxmi, Mumbai, fetched ₹2,250 crore. This record price reflects strong investor confidence in Mumbai's real estate. Dineshchandra R Agrawal Infracon made the winning bid. The land will be leased for 99 years. This development highlights the demand for strategic urban land.

news.title: USA: Blackstone's LivCor settles DOJ's rental price fixing claims
news.para: The US Justice Department has reached a settlement with LivCor, a subsidiary of Blackstone. Accused of colluding with fellow landlords to artificially inflate rent prices by using software to share sensitive pricing data, LivCor's agreement emphasizes a shift towards transparency.

news.title: Pune: PMC to generate ₹200 crore annually by granting building permissions in merged areas
news.para: Pune Municipal Corporation anticipates generating Rs 200 crore annually from building permissions in newly merged areas. This revenue will fund crucial infrastructure projects, including sewage and water supply networks, to address the needs of a growing population. The transfer of authority from PMRDA aims to streamline civic service delivery and accelerate development plans.

news.title: Delhi civic body expedites work on its fifth C&D waste plant in Tehkhand
news.para: Delhi is boosting its waste management with a new construction and demolition waste processing plant in Tehkhand, set to be operational within a year. This fifth plant, along with four existing ones, will significantly increase the city's daily processing capacity.

news.title: Shree Cement withdraws lockout at Baloda Bazar plant in Raipur
news.para: After a brief four-day lockout that commenced on December 18, 2025, Shree Cement has reopened its Baloda Bazar facility in Raipur, Chhattisgarh. The company and its workers have reached a constructive agreement, paving the way for the resumption of regular cement production.

news.title: RG Group completes stalled Greater Noida West housing project after insolvency
news.para: RG Group announces the completion of phase 1 in their RG Luxury Homes project located in Greater Noida West. After overcoming insolvency challenges, with construction costs evaluated at ₹200 crore, they have managed to refund ₹95 crore to affected homebuyers.

news.title: Germany's residential property prices up 3.3% in July-September 2025
news.para: The German housing market is on the rise again, with prices climbing for the fourth consecutive quarter. This rebound follows a period of decline, showcasing a renewed interest in both urban and suburban living. Notably, single-family and duplex homes in cities have experienced the steepest price hikes, while even rural regions are enjoying notable increases.

news.title: Vanke may adopt a familiar playbook in China to tackle debt crisis, say analysts
news.para: China Vanke is grappling with urgent bond repayment issues as investors have firmly rejected requests for payment delays. Experts anticipate a series of extension attempts leading up to a necessary restructuring of debts. This situation is pivotal in assessing governmental support for firms in distress.

news.title: Pune land deal: Parth Pawar's firm files civil suit seeking cancellation of sale deed
news.para: Amadea Enterprises LLP, co-founded by Parth Pawar, is taking action against the sale of a contentious 40-acre plot in Mundhwa, which was sold for Rs 300 crore and is believed to belong to the government.
